(2, 'Jabong.com', 'Jabong', '2014-08-14', '<div id="footer">\r\n<ul id="footer-icons" class="noprint">\r\n<li id="footer-poweredbyico">\r\n<p>The site started operations in January 2012. It was co-founded by Arun Chandra Mohan, Praveen Sinha, and Lakshmi Potluri after which Manu Jain, and Mukul Bafana joined the organization.<sup id="cite_ref-Times_of_India_2-1" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jabong.com#cite_note-Times_of_India-2">[2]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-Venture_Finance_5-0" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jabong.com#cite_note-Venture_Finance-5">[5]</a></sup>&nbsp;The managing officers are Arun Chandra Mohan and Praveen Sinha.<sup id="cite_ref-Techcircle_6-0" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jabong.com#cite_note-Techcircle-6">[6]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-BBC_7-0" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jabong.com#cite_note-BBC-7">[7]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-The_Financial_Express_8-0" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jabong.com#cite_note-The_Financial_Express-8">[8]</a></sup></p>\r\n<p>In March 2013, Jabong was shipping 6000-7000 orders a day.<sup id="cite_ref-Forbes_9-0" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jabong.com#cite_note-Forbes-9">[9]</a></sup>&nbsp;In March 2013, the annual revenues of Jabong was estimated to be 100-150 mn USD.<sup id="cite_ref-The_Economist_10-0" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jabong.com#cite_note-The_Economist-10">[10]</a></sup>&nbsp;During September 2013 Jabong was shipping 14,000 orders on a daily basis out of which 60% were from small towns.<sup id="cite_ref-Livemint_11-0" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jabong.com#cite_note-Livemint-11">[11]</a></sup>&nbsp;During July 2014, Jabong was shipping close to 80,000 orders on a daily basis.<sup class="noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact">[<em><a title="Wikipedia:Citation needed" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources. (August 2014)">citation needed</span></a></em>]</sup></p>\r\n<p>Jabong was one of the most visited e-commerce sites during the&nbsp;<a title="Great Online Shopping Festival" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Great_Online_Shopping_Festival">Great Online Shopping Festival</a>&nbsp;2013. Company representatives claimed that its revenues increased five to six times compared to a usual day, and that Jabong set a record for sale in the male fashion category.<sup id="cite_ref-TimesofIndia_12-0" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jabong.com#cite_note-TimesofIndia-12">[12]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-Exchange_4_Media_13-0" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jabong.com#cite_note-Exchange_4_Media-13">[13]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-IndianExpress_14-0" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jabong.com#cite_note-IndianExpress-14">[14]</a></sup></p>\r\n<p>Manu Jain left Jabong and joined Xiaomi India.&nbsp;<sup id="cite_ref-15" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jabong.com#cite_note-15">[15]</a></sup></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', '2014-08-28 14:04:20', '2014-08-29 20:14:08'),
(3, 'Fabfurnish.com', 'Fabfurnish', '2014-08-13', '<p><strong>FabFurnish.com</strong><span>&nbsp;is an Indian brand in furniture &amp; home d&eacute;cor founded in 2012. FabFurnish.com retails online, and has showrooms in India as well. The company offers a huge range of furniture, furnishings, d&eacute;cor and kitchenware from an array of top Indian and International brands as well as its own private label.</span></p>\r\n<h2><span id="History" class="mw-headline">History</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a title="Edit section: History" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=FabFurnish.com&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\r\n<p>FabFurnish.com was launched in March, 2012 by Vaibhav Aggarwal, Vikram Chopra and Mehul Agrawal. The company is fully owned by&nbsp;<a title="Rocket Internet" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rocket_Internet">Rocket Internet</a>, a German incubator which has multiple ecommerce ventures across various countries such as&nbsp;<a title="Zalando" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zalando">Zalando</a>&nbsp;in Germany, Dafiti in Brazil, Iconic in Australia, Jabong in India and Lamoda in Russia. In June, 2012 FabFurnish.com acquired Heavenandhome, another Rocket venture, to create a single destination for home d&eacute;cor. The company aims to replicate IKEA model online in India.<sup id="cite_ref-TheHinduBusinessLine.com_2-0" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FabFurnish.com#cite_note-TheHinduBusinessLine.com-2">[2]</a></sup></p>\r\n<p>The e-store initially started with 2000 products and since then has scaled to an assortment of over 60,000 products. In Dec 2012, it launched its first franchise store in Gurgaon. The brand has introduced 3 more stores in Bangalore and Faridabad since then.</p>\r\n<p>To make furniture shopping<sup id="cite_ref-MoneyControl.com_3-0" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FabFurnish.com#cite_note-MoneyControl.com-3">[3]</a></sup>&nbsp;convenient for customers, FabFurnish.com also started a unique part- payment method in Jan 2013 wherein a customer can pay only some amount upfront and the remaining at the time of delivery. It also offers convenient EMI options through multiple partnerships with banks.</p>\r\n<p>In May 2013, FabFurnish.com launched a 360 degree view feature that allows customer to see the furniture from all angles through flick of the mouse.</p>\r\n<p>The brand introduced its mobile site m.FabFurnish.com for giving its customers the convenience of shopping through mobile in June, 2013 and the facility of mobile check out in Jan, 2014.</p>', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2014-08-29 20:15:48'),
(4, 'StarCj.com', 'StarCj', '2014-08-05', '<p><span>Festive time of the year is here and the celebration is incomplete without loads and loads of shopping. Introducing to you - Ganesh Chaturthi Season Sale. Happy&nbsp;</span><strong>...</strong><span>&nbsp;</span></p>', '2014-08-13 00:00:00', '2014-08-29 20:16:40'),
(5, 'Myntra.com', 'Myntra', '2014-08-13', '<p><strong>Myntra.com</strong>&nbsp;is an Indian online shopping retailer of fashion and casual lifestyle products, headquartered in&nbsp;<a class="mw-redirect" title="Bangalore, Karnataka" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bangalore,_Karnataka">Bangalore, Karnataka</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myntra.com#cite_note-2">[2]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myntra.com#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup>&nbsp;<sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myntra.com#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup></p>\r\n<p>On 22nd May 2014&nbsp;<a title="Flipkart" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flipkart">Flipkart</a>&nbsp;acquired Myntra in a deal estimated to be around $300 Mn.<sup id="cite_ref-5" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myntra.com#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-bp_6-0" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myntra.com#cite_note-bp-6">[6]</a></sup></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div id="toc" class="toc">&nbsp;\r\n<h2><span id="History" class="mw-headline">History</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a title="Edit section: History" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Myntra.com&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\r\n<p>Myntra was established by Mukesh Bansal in February 2007 with a vision of creating India''s largest on-demand personalization portal.<sup id="cite_ref-7" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myntra.com#cite_note-7">[7]</a></sup></p>\r\n<p>Myntra is headquartered in Bangalore and has been funded by leading Venture Capital funds like Tiger, Kalaari, PremjiInvest, IDG &amp; Accel Partners.<sup id="cite_ref-8" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myntra.com#cite_note-8">[8]</a></sup></p>\r\n<p>From 2007 to December 2010, Myntra.com was in the business of personalization of products online.<sup id="cite_ref-9" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myntra.com#cite_note-9">[9]</a></sup>&nbsp;The products ranged from T-shirts, mugs, greeting cards, calendars, key chains, diaries etc. However, in 2010, the company expanded its catalogue to retail fashion and lifestyle products.</p>\r\n<h3><span id="Products" class="mw-headline">Products</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a title="Edit section: Products" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Myntra.com&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\r\n<p>Myntra.com currently offers close to 70,000 products from more than 700 leading Indian, international and designer brands.<sup id="cite_ref-10" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myntra.com#cite_note-10">[10]</a></sup>&nbsp;The portal receives over 50 million hits every month and services over 9,000 pin codes across the country.<sup id="cite_ref-11" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myntra.com#cite_note-11">[11]</a></sup></p>\r\n<p>In 2013, Myntra acquired San-Francisco-based Fitiquette, a developer of virtual fitting room technology.<sup id="cite_ref-12" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myntra.com#cite_note-12">[12]</a></sup></p>\r\n<p>In November 2013, Bollywood star Hrithik Roshan joined forces with online shopping portal Myntra.com to exclusively launch and manufacture his active lifestyle apparel and casual wear brand HRX.<sup id="cite_ref-13" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myntra.com#cite_note-13">[13]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-14" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myntra.com#cite_note-14">[14]</a></sup></p>\r\n</div>', '2014-08-05 00:00:00', '2014-08-29 20:15:11'),
(6, 'Flipkart.com', 'Flipkart', '2014-08-28', '<div class="_cgc kno-fb-ctx">\r\n<div class="kno-rdesc">Flipkart is an e-commerce company founded in 2007, by Sachin and Binny Bansal. It operates exclusively in India, where it is headquartered in Bangalore, Karnataka. It is registered in Singapore, and owned by a Singapore-based holding company.&nbsp;<a class="fl q _KCd" href="https://www.google.co.in/url?sa=t&amp;rct=j&amp;q=&amp;esrc=s&amp;source=web&amp;cd=18&amp;ved=0CJgBEJoTKAAwEQ&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FFlipkart&amp;ei=VsAAVOy8OIqxuAT3hIKACg&amp;usg=AFQjCNH5-DyvgDsmmmdv5VsYbFRhPW76gw&amp;sig2=B1uStSeRhh9uKQx31VnOjQ" target="_blank"><span class="_tWc">Wikipedia</span></a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li class="mod">\r\n<div class="_eFb">\r\n<div class="_mr kno-fb-ctx"><span class="_xdb"><a class="fl" href="https://www.google.co.in/search?newwindow=1&amp;safe=off&amp;es_sm=122&amp;q=flipkart+customer+service&amp;stick=H4sIAAAAAAAAAGOovnz8BQMDgwsHnxCXfq6-QXJRSlVFgZZJdrKVfn5RemJeZlViSWZ-HgrHKrm0uCQ_N7VIoTi1qCwzOVWhICM_LzVz_fLuSz6PL1QYP_i78017nUXJlGgAwTxaQmEAAAA&amp;sa=X&amp;ei=VsAAVOy8OIqxuAT3hIKACg&amp;ved=0CJ4BEOgTKAEwEw">Customer service</a>:&nbsp;</span><span class="kno-fv _lgc">080 4940 0000</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class="mod">\r\n<div class="_eFb">\r\n<div class="_mr kno-fb-ctx"><span class="_xdb"><a class="fl" href="https://www.google.co.in/search?newwindow=1&amp;safe=off&amp;es_sm=122&amp;q=flipkart+founded&amp;stick=H4sIAAAAAAAAAGOovnz8BQMDgykHnxCXfq6-QXJRSlVFgZZqdrKVfn5RemJeZlViSWZ-HgrHKi2_NC8lNWUP_49zF5Nq_6nVT709OWn7AYmoincAK_6FBFIAAAA&amp;sa=X&amp;ei=VsAAVOy8OIqxuAT3hIKACg&amp;ved=0CKIBEOgTKAEwFA">Founded</a>:&nbsp;</span><span class="kno-fv _lgc">September 5, 2007</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class="mod">\r\n<div class="_eFb">\r\n<div class="_mr kno-fb-ctx"><span class="_xdb"><a class="fl" href="https://www.google.co.in/search?newwindow=1&amp;safe=off&amp;es_sm=122&amp;q=flipkart+ceo&amp;stick=H4sIAAAAAAAAA